The paper discusses the development of AI agents to support decision-making processes, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on understanding the behavior of these agents, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of different models for policy summarization, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of carefully considering user models in policy summarization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
